<item>
            <title>[OAK-55] Provide reasonable way to set property on NodeStateEditor</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-55</link>
                <project id="12313221" key="OAK">Jackrabbit Oak</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;currently properties are add/modified on the NodeStateEditor using:     void setProperty(PropertyState state);&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;the consequence of that is that every single usage of that method needs to know the details&lt;br/&gt;
of how to create a property state. IMO that&apos;s really bad practice and should be refactored.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;i would suggest to change it to something like &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;setProperty(String name, Scalar value)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;setProperty(String name, List&amp;lt;Scalar&amp;gt; values)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</description>
